HEADWORD: Lanugo
<hw>La*nu"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Lanuginose</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The soft woolly hair
which covers most parts of the mammal fetus, and in man is shed before
or soon after birth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

